ting**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I can place a non-test helper in the same package under src/test/java to access package-private methods. The guidelines say to keep tests outside the library’s packages, but maybe a helper isn't really a test? \\n\\nHowever, the focus is on having a dedicated Java test file. It seems I can't include package org.objenesis in the same file because it's under the COM package. Should I add a second file instead? That might be the best way to go.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting task progress**\\n\\nI see that the latest successful coverage didn’t include everything it should have. I think it’s important to inspect the logs after the second attempt. Maybe I should consider building reports to analyze what went wrong. Testing the result might help clarify things too. Let's see what insights I can gather from this. It feels like there’s a lot to unpack here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qcFts3LxQ5snrtUD0GaBZI4k|fc_02f61b83073783bd0169ef718e08108190a3e4d5b16e16012b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/1.2/build/test-results -type f -name '*.xml' -print -exec rg -n \"JRockit131|failure|error|resolves\" {} \\; | head -200", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1427, "output": 835, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40662, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777299839765, "responseId": "resp_02f61b83073783bd0169ef718085608190a0fa2964984fc552"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_qcFts3LxQ5snrtUD0GaBZI4k|fc_02f61b83073783bd0169ef718e08108190a3e4d5b16e16012b", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/1.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_objenesis.objenesis.ObjectStreamClassInstantiatorTest.xml\n2:<testsuite name=\"org_objenesis.objenes